===Adjective===
'''linoleic'''
#The word linoleic comes from the Greek word linon (flax). Oleic means of, relating to, or derived from oil or of or relating to oleic acid.
#Of, or derived from [[linoleum]], or [[linseed]] [[oil]]
#{{chemistry}} designating an [[organic]] [[fatty acid]], a thin yellow oil, found [[combined]] as an [[ester]] of [[glycerol]] in oils of linseed, [[poppy]], [[hemp]], and certain [[nut]]s; it is a [[polyunsaturated]] fatty acid with 18 [[carbon]] atoms and two [[double bond]]s.
